Testablauf:
1.Step: dev uses git command
dev in terminal
    cd home/user/myProject
    git checkout featureX
git executes
    checkout().call branch
    run .git/hooks/post-checkout
2.Step: post-checkout hook (bash script) runs
    #!/bin/bash
    REPO_ROOT=$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)
    TRIGGER_FILE="$REPO_ROOT/.vitruvius/reload-trigger"

    # Create trigger file
    echo "Reload requested at: $(date)" > "$TRIGGER_FILE"

    result:
    file created at .vitruvius/reload-trigger
3.Step: VsumReloadWatcher detects trigger
VsumReloadWatcher
    detects if .vitruvius/reload-trigger file exists
    call postCheckoutHandler.onBranchSwitch()
4.Step; reload vsum
PostCheckoutHandler:
    call virtualModel.reload()
VirtualModel
    reloads vsum by unloading models from memory and loading new models


dev types git checkout featureX in terminal
git updates all files on disk to match the featureX branch
git automatically runs the post-checkout hook (bash script)
hook creates a trigger file: .vitruvius/reload-trigger
watcher detects this file
watcher deletes the trigger and calls PostCheckoutHandler
PostCheckoutHandler calls VirtualModel.reload()
reload clears memory and loads models from disk (which git just updated)
vsum now has the correct models for featureX branch